		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=160279"><span id=Scholar>Kagain</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>48 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.99]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>All i had to do was look at your equipment to tell that you were an int-caster twinking out an ogre/troll warrior.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you want to be a good warrior (which means that you are a capable tank that people will actually want in a group)  You are going to have to start changing your equipment around level 35.  After that, your high STR and STA won't hide the fact that your AC would just be horrendous for a main tank.   And unfortunately, Wurmslayer (or Centi LS) don't taunt a fraction as well as a Lamentation in the hands of any warrior worth his salt.  So if you want to be a good warrior and actually break the mold that INT caster twinks have made for themselves, it might be wise to follow at least some of my advice.  <br><br>Get rid of the Crusty armor and trade it in for Crafted (or anything with more AC).  Sure the stats look nice, but stats don't keep you from dying, AC does.  Crusty helm should be replaced by the Skull Shaped Barbute, a staple for warriors for a long time just because it's probably got the best effectiveness-to-price ratio on anything.  Your chest should be replaced by a Tree Weave.  Not only does tree weave have high AC (25) but it also adds 10 strength.  You should be looking to buy some of the cheaper Cobalt pieces (depending on your server) like the gloves, boots, and shoulders (Your wizard could fight in KC and Seb and loot some also).  FBSS is actually a good waist because the only other slot that you can reasonably find haste on are gloves (Silver Chitin Handwraps and Sporali Gloves).  AC is MUCH easier to come by on gloves than waist, so FBSS makes a good choice. *NOTE - FBSS and SCHW are generally known to have the same percentage of haste, or very close to the same percentage*  There is no question about it, you NEED the 6ac 65hp rings.  AC and HP keep you alive, and that's your mission :).  In secondary, you can use Centi Longsword or preferably a Venomous Axe of the Velium Brood an 11dmg 24dly weapon that adds 10ac and procs an 85DD quite often.  Good masks that are cheap are Antlered Mask and Grotesque Alloy Mask.  Goranga Idol is a decent range slot that is pretty cheap.<br><br>Remember that you don't have to begin doing this until around level 35.  Until then you should use Smoldering Brand in primary until you get past 20 because the damage cap makes wurmslayer 10dmg 40dly which is quite crappy for a twink.  You'll be the bane of Crushbone with your stats now, but just remember that sooner or later you are going to have to realize that AC is a warrior's GOD.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Kagain Warfiend<br>56 Dwarf Warrior<br>Eternal Heroes<br>Tribunal<br><br>Kalgoth<br>21Samurai/30Warrior/15Thief<br>BBCGamingNetwork<br>Quetzalcoatl<br><br>Kalgoth<br>Swordsman/Creature Handler<br>*BBC|GamingNetwork<br>Sunrunner</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
