		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.97]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>As someone already said, toss all the crusty. Remember, you are supposed to be the meat shield, and your primary role is to TAKE damage, and keep taunt, not deal out the damage. Get the Lammy NOW. if you are still lvl 1, a lammy will outdamage (and more important, outtaunt) just about anything, with a few exceptions. Once you hit 20, a wurmy could be fun for about 10 levels, but no reason for it really.<br><br>While treeweave is a good suggestion, Barbed ringmail is even better for chest. I'd go ahead and get the barbed ringmail legs too. As well as a combination of barbed ringmail and cobalt for the other slots, where you can get it.<br><br>For cheaper stuff, gauntlets of the black are great for hands, and crafted is still better than crusty in the other slots. I'd say probably go for the fbss for waist, if price is a concern, because it is about half the price of SCHW. <br><br>Another alternative, if you have a group of friends about your level, is to talk them into hunting icewell keep, if dwarf faction isn't a concern, and then let your warrior loot the royal velium frosted pieces that drop. harder route, since they are no-drop, but good armor.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jul 17 23:38:50 2002</em></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=1><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=1&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=102